FBIS3-42409 "jpuma005___94008" JPRS-UMA-94-005 Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Central Eurasia Military Affairs 9 February 1994 CIS/RUSSIAN MILITARY ISSUES GROUND TROOPS PZM-2 Regimental Earth-Mover 94UM0180A Moscow VOYENNYY VESTNIK in Russian No 9, Sep 1993 p C3 94UM0180A Moscow VOYENNYY VESTNIK Language: Russian Article Type:CSO [Unattributed article, under the rubric: "Engineer Munitions and Equipment Systems": "PZM-2"] [Text] The PZM-2 Regimental Earth-Mover is designed for engineer preparation of terrain. It consists of a wheeled prime mover, a bucket-less earthmoving tool and a winch. Tactical-Technical Specifications Dimensions of an excavated trench, meters: Depth 1.2 Width along the top: in thawed earth 0.9 in frozen earth 0.65 Width along the bottom 0.65 Dimensions of excavated foundation pits, meters: Width 2-3.5 Depth up to 3 Productive capacity: While excavating foundation pits, 100-140 m[.sup]3[/] per hour While excavating trenches, meters per up to 140 hour Transport speed, kph up to 45 Weight, tonnes 12.8 Crew, men 2 COPYRIGHT: VOYENNYY VESTNIK No 9 1993
